    <section class="font-body text-on-surface leading-relaxed space-y-6">
      <p>For most Malaysian e-commerce and product businesses, the packaging question eventually becomes: should we go custom? Custom branded boxes cost more upfront. They require minimum order quantities and longer lead times. So is the investment actually worth it — or is it just a nice-to-have that successful brands do once they already have cash flow?</p>

      <p>This guide cuts through the theory and looks at the real return on investment (ROI) of custom carton boxes for Malaysian SMEs, with practical numbers and a framework for deciding when the switch makes sense.</p>

      <h2 class="font-headline text-2xl font-bold text-on-surface mt-10 mb-4">What Does Custom Branded Packaging Actually Cost in Malaysia?</h2>
      <p>The base cost of plain corrugated carton boxes in Malaysia runs from approximately RM 1.90 to RM 6.50 per box depending on size and wall type. Custom printed boxes — with your logo, brand colours, and text — typically add 20–40% to this unit cost. There is also usually a one-off plate or setup fee for the print design, typically RM 500–1,500 depending on the number of colours and print faces.</p>

      <h3 class="font-headline text-xl font-semibold text-on-surface mt-6 mb-3">Break-Even Analysis: A Simple Example</h3>
      <p>Suppose a plain medium box costs RM 2.50 and a custom printed equivalent costs RM 3.20 — a difference of RM 0.70 per box. If you order 1,000 boxes with a RM 1,000 setup fee, your total extra cost is RM 700 (unit premium) + RM 1,000 (setup) = RM 1,700 above plain boxes. To break even purely on packaging cost, you need the branded box to deliver at least RM 1.70 additional value per order. That can come from higher prices, repeat purchases, or reduced marketing spend — all real and measurable outcomes.</p>

      <h2 class="font-headline text-2xl font-bold text-on-surface mt-10 mb-4">The Revenue Side: How Custom Packaging Generates Returns</h2>

