        <div class="space-y-3 font-body text-sm">
          <div class="flex justify-between items-start py-2 border-b border-outline-variant/20">
            <span class="font-semibold text-on-surface">Higher perceived value</span>
            <span class="text-secondary text-right max-w-xs">Customers willing to pay 5–15% more for same product in branded packaging vs. plain box</span>
          </div>
          <div class="flex justify-between items-start py-2 border-b border-outline-variant/20">
            <span class="font-semibold text-on-surface">Repeat purchase rate</span>
            <span class="text-secondary text-right max-w-xs">Branded unboxing creates brand recall; customers more likely to search your brand next time vs. generic</span>
          </div>
          <div class="flex justify-between items-start py-2 border-b border-outline-variant/20">
            <span class="font-semibold text-on-surface">Social sharing (UGC)</span>
            <span class="text-secondary text-right max-w-xs">Attractive packages get shared on Instagram, TikTok — free reach worth RM hundreds per post</span>
          </div>
          <div class="flex justify-between items-start py-2">
            <span class="font-semibold text-on-surface">Trust & professionalism</span>
            <span class="text-secondary text-right max-w-xs">Branded packaging reduces buyer's remorse and negative reviews from "looks cheap" complaints</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="font-headline text-2xl font-bold text-on-surface mt-10 mb-4">Who Should Switch to Custom Packaging Now?</h2>
      <p>Custom packaging makes clear financial sense when your order volumes are consistent and growing, your product price point is RM 30 or higher (where packaging premium is a small % of total purchase), and your customers share products visually (lifestyle, beauty, fashion, food). Businesses selling B2B products or pure commodities typically see less return from branded packaging since the purchase decision is rational rather than emotional.</p>

      <h3 class="font-headline text-xl font-semibold text-on-surface mt-6 mb-3">The Middle Path: Branded Stickers on Plain Boxes</h3>
      <p>For businesses not ready for full custom print runs, a cost-effective middle option is using plain boxes with branded stickers or custom tissue paper inside. This costs less than custom printed boxes while still creating a more branded feel than a plain brown box. It is especially popular among boutique fashion and artisan food sellers in Malaysia.</p>

      <h2 class="font-headline text-2xl font-bold text-on-surface mt-10 mb-4">Timing Your Switch to Custom Boxes</h2>
      <p>The right moment to invest in custom boxes is when you are shipping more than 200–300 orders per month consistently. At that volume, the per-unit cost premium is manageable, your design investment is spread across meaningful quantity, and the brand-building effect compounds over time. Quinocycle can supply both plain boxes now and help you plan your transition to custom printed packaging as your business grows.</p>

